# 🧠 MindTrack – Setup & Run Guide

AI-Driven Mental Health Sentiment & Trend Analysis for Personal Journals.

---

## 1. Project Structure

```
mindtrack/
├── app.py                  ← Streamlit entry point (run this)
├── model_engine.py         ← PyTorch / HuggingFace inference engine
├── requirements.txt
├── model/                  ← ⬅ Put your model files here
│   ├── config.json         (already have this)
│   ├── tokenizer.json      (already have this)
│   └── pytorch_model.bin   (download – see Step 3)
└── pages_ui/
    ├── nav.py              ← Shared sidebar
    ├── login_page.py
    ├── dashboard_page.py   ← Journal entry + live analysis
    ├── analytics_page.py   ← Charts & trends
    └── settings_page.py
```

---

## 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## 3. Place Your Model Files

Copy `config.json` and `tokenizer.json` (already uploaded) into a `model/` folder:

```bash
mkdir model
cp config.json   model/
cp tokenizer.json model/
```

Then download the matching weights. Since `config.json` is a
**DistilRoBERTa** 6-class emotion classifier, the compatible HuggingFace
model is `bhadresh-savani/distilroberta-base-emotion`:

```bash
python - <<'EOF'
from transformers import AutoModelForSequenceClassification
m = AutoModelForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(
        "bhadresh-savani/distilroberta-base-emotion")
m.save_pretrained("./model")
EOF
```

> If you have your own fine-tuned `pytorch_model.bin`, copy it into `model/`
> instead of running the download above.

---

## 4. Run the App

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

Open http://localhost:8501 in your browser.

---

## 5. Demo Login

Any username + any password ≥ 4 characters will work in demo mode.
Replace the auth logic in `pages_ui/login_page.py` with real DB auth.

---

## 6. Custom Model Path

Set the env variable if your model lives elsewhere:

```bash
MINDTRACK_MODEL_DIR=/path/to/model streamlit run app.py
```

---

## Architecture

```
User types journal entry
        ↓
  Streamlit (app.py)
        ↓
  model_engine.predict(text)
        ↓
  AutoTokenizer  →  tokenize
        ↓
  DistilRoBERTa  →  6-class logits
        ↓
  Softmax  →  emotion probabilities
        ↓
  Wellness Index  +  Alert flag
        ↓
  Streamlit Dashboard / Analytics
```
